			<h2 class="comments-title">
			8 thoughts on &ldquo;The Fall&rdquo;		</h2>

		
		<ol class="comment-list">
					<li id="comment-419" class="comment byuser comment-author-rudyneeser even thread-even depth-1 parent">
			<article id="div-comment-419" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/?s=56&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/?s=112&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-56 photo avatar-default' height='56' width='56' />						<b class="fn"><a href='http://rudyneeser.wordpress.com/' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>Rudy Neeser</a></b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="http://localhost:8888/microfiction.co.za/2010/08/22/the-fall/#comment-419">
							<time datetime="2010-08-25T18:36:39+00:00">
								August 25, 2010 at 6:36 pm							</time>
						</a>
											</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>This is about a bird that has just been hunted; struck by an arrow it falls to the ground.</p>
<p>Lovely, descriptive piece. I enjoyed the repetition in the first and last paragraphs. It ties together the circle of a bird hunted for its feathers by an arrow with (I assume) feather fletching.</p>
<p>I was slightly unsure whether the description of the feathers (the ones laced with silver) was the bird&#8217;s feathers, the arrows feathers, or — as I like to think — both, in the different paragraphs. Also, in the last paragraph, cloth is mentioned: I&#8217;m not sure what the cloth is in relation to <img src="http://localhost:8888/microfiction.co.za/wp-includes/images/smilies/frownie.png" alt=":(" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> </p>
<p>&gt; The force of its fall pulled its wings and body into grotesque<br />
&gt; shapes, brutally moulded by the air currents which the bird had<br />
&gt; previously mastered.<br />
Great sentence <img src="http://localhost:8888/microfiction.co.za/wp-includes/images/smilies/simple-smile.png" alt=":)" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /></p>
<p>&gt; Its feathers, ironically, seemed<br />
I don&#8217;t think that &#8220;ironically&#8221; adds much.</p>
<p>Cool piece. Thanks for sharing <img src="http://localhost:8888/microfiction.co.za/wp-includes/images/smilies/simple-smile.png" alt=":)" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /></p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

				<div class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='http://localhost:8888/microfiction.co.za/2010/08/22/the-fall/?replytocom=419#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm( "div-comment-419", "419", "respond", "212" )' aria-label='Reply to Rudy Neeser'>Reply</a></div>			</article><!-- .comment-body -->
