						</a>
											</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Thanks for the comments. I actually only meant the first feathers description to be about the bird. Now I see that it can be about both the bird and the arrow, and I really like that duality. Thanks for pointing it out <img src="http://localhost:8888/microfiction.co.za/wp-includes/images/smilies/simple-smile.png" alt=":-)" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /> </p>
<p>I meant the last paragraph to be the bird&#8217;s feathers now sewn into an article of clothing; hence the cloth. On re-examination, it isn&#8217;t as clear as I would like it to be.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

