		<li id="comment-420" class="comment byuser comment-author-elementalsystems even thread-odd thread-alt depth-1 parent">
			<article id="div-comment-420" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/?s=56&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='http://2.gravatar.com/avatar/?s=112&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-56 photo avatar-default' height='56' width='56' />						<b class="fn"><a href='http://elementsrevisited.wordpress.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>elementalsystems</a></b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="http://localhost:8888/microfiction.co.za/2010/08/22/the-fall/#comment-420">
							<time datetime="2010-08-27T09:29:51+00:00">
								August 27, 2010 at 9:29 am							</time>
						</a>
											</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Really like the wordy descriptive bits &#8211; especially the second and third paragraphs. Also the description of the still bird lying on the ground gives a clear visual image.</p>
<p>Like the connections between the beginning and the end and the repetition/comparison between the deadly feathers on the arrow, the feathers on the living bird and feathers sown onto something in the last paragraph. Love the dancing threads of silver in both contexts.</p>
<p>I have a logical problem with this sentence:<br />
When its body first brushed the treetops, the bird was already dead, its neck broken from the violence of its catastrophic fall.<br />
How did it break its neck before brushing the treetops? Its not the fall that is violent only the stop :).</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

				<div class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='http://localhost:8888/microfiction.co.za/2010/08/22/the-fall/?replytocom=420#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm( "div-comment-420", "420", "respond", "212" )' aria-label='Reply to elementalsystems'>Reply</a></div>			</article><!-- .comment-body -->
