		<li id="comment-424" class="comment byuser comment-author-cbraz bypostauthor odd alt depth-2">
			<article id="div-comment-424" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/?s=56&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='http://1.gravatar.com/avatar/?s=112&amp;d=mm&amp;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-56 photo avatar-default' height='56' width='56' />						<b class="fn">cbraz</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="http://localhost:8888/microfiction.co.za/2010/08/22/the-fall/#comment-424">
							<time datetime="2010-08-30T15:10:05+00:00">
								August 30, 2010 at 3:10 pm							</time>
						</a>
											</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Thanks for the comments. I’m glad that you found it beautiful and evocative.</p>
<p>I looked again at my adverbs and agree with you on some of them – the piece would have been stronger without ironically or brilliantly, and I prefer your violence to mine <img src="http://localhost:8888/microfiction.co.za/wp-includes/images/smilies/simple-smile.png" alt=":-)" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /></p>
<p>I also appreciate the economy suggestions as I have a tendency to be long-winded. The only one I don’t agree with is “There was an odd elegance in the final position of the broken bones and scattered feathers.” I wanted to focus this paragraph on the bird (in contrast to the next sentence where it is no longer and only the feathers are there) and the change removes it from focus too much.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

				<div class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='http://localhost:8888/microfiction.co.za/2010/08/22/the-fall/?replytocom=424#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm( "div-comment-424", "424", "respond", "212" )' aria-label='Reply to cbraz'>Reply</a></div>			</article><!-- .comment-body -->
