				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Very nice, really enjoyed it. <img src="http://localhost:8888/microfiction.co.za/wp-includes/images/smilies/simple-smile.png" alt=":)" class="wp-smiley" style="height: 1em; max-height: 1em;" /><br />
The circle created by the opening and the ending are particularly sweet.<br />
I got great <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Henri_Cartier-Bresson#The_Decisive_Moment" rel="nofollow">decisive moment</a> / slice of life vibes from this. Like catching a view of something important that we wouldn&#8217;t have seen otherwise.</p>
<p>+1 for dropping &#8220;ironically,&#8221; for personal preference and flow.<br />
I also had problems with the logic of violence of fall vs stop, but it&#8217;s a minor quibble.</p>
<p>You&#8217;ve swirled the beauty of the feathers and the grotesqueness of the death together very well.</p>
<p>Kewl!</p>
